Vercel Deployment Plan: Merging Backend and Frontend-Admin
Executive Summary
Based on analysis of the NeureCore project structure, I've created a comprehensive plan to deploy both the NestJS backend and Next.js frontend-admin as a single Vercel application. The plan addresses key challenges including WebSocket limitations, database connectivity, and serverless adaptation.

Recommended Architecture: Option 1 (NestJS with Vercel Serverless Adapter)
Decision: Use @vercel/serverless-adapter to convert NestJS to Vercel functions while keeping frontend-admin as Next.js.

Why This Approach:
Minimal code changes to existing NestJS backend
Full NestJS capabilities preserved
Better separation of concerns
Easier migration path
